author: Jacob Davey
title: Stefan Kholi’s ‘100 HOURS in LA’ Captures Big Sean, Metro Boomin & More
text:
Visit the original post to see all 6 images from this gallery. 
We’ve got the first look at Stefan Kohli first installment in his 100 HOURS series, which begins with some vibrant photos of your favorite musicians enjoying summertime LA.
The gallery includes some up-close and personal shots of some of hip-hop’s best artists kicking it in the settings of studios and vintage cars, including Big Sean, Metro Boomin, MadeInTyo and Cousin Stizz, as well as friends and associates such as Jeh-Mahk and Leano. MadeInTyo is notably stunting in some fresh Pastelle and Ian Connor’s Revenge sneakers.
The series will continue to “capture the vibe of trips to different cities filled with shooting, exploring, and drawing inspiration from every city’s unique energy,” according to Stefan, who is currently working with Ariana Grande.
Check out the gallery of photos above for a taster of what’s in store. For a full look at all the photos from the installment, head to the Photokohli website .
In related music news, Metro Boomin has recently announced plans to create his own record label. Get the scoop here .
